8 November 2016Minister Faith Muthambi as a member of the Inter- Ministerial Committee (IMC) on Elections is visiting Limpopo today for the Municipal by-Elections to be held on Wednesday, 9 November 2016.In Limpopo the by Elections will be held in two wards.Ward 3 in LIM 345- New Municipality with 4781 registered voters with became vacant as a result of the death of the councillor. Voting will take place at the following stations:Ward 10 in LIM 354- Polokwane with 7893 registered voters which became vacant as a result of the resignation of the councillor.Voting will take place at the following stations:Members of the media are encouraged to cover the by-elections.Enquiries: Ayanda Holo Cell: 061 488 0634Issued by Department of Communications